The paper deals with a fundamental packing problem in discrete optimization, which is a topic studied in computer science theory. The problem is strongly NP-hard, indicating that it belongs to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper proposes a new algorithmic approach to the problem, which involves sparsification techniques and integer programming, suggesting that it belongs to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents a new structural result that may have applications to other settings, indicating that it belongs to the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT).
